text.section:
In addition to powers and authorities otherwise granted the Kentucky Economic Development Finance Authority, the authority may:
Make and condition loans from the fund as required by state or federal law;
Enter into any necessary or required agreement and give or make any necessary or required assurance or certification with any person or entity to receive payments or to make or to provide loans;
Guarantee or purchase insurance for obligations of the fund where the action would improve credit market access or reduce interest rates;
Receive money from any public or private source to implement the purposes of this section;
Approve or reject applications made to it for loans from the fund, and establish standards applicable thereto;
Provide for the issuance of revenue bonds and bond anticipation notes as prescribed by KRS 154.10-035 for the purposes as set forth in this section;
Promulgate administrative regulations implementing the purposes of this section in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A; and
Do all things necessary and convenient to achieve the objectives and purposes of this section which are not otherwise prohibited by state law.
